The paper deals with a problem in network analysis and graph theory, specifically the problem of finding an alpha-optimal reassembling of a simple graph. This falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The algorithm presented in the paper is designed to work specifically for 3-regular plane graphs, which suggests that computational geometry (cs.CG) may also be a relevant sub-category. The paper also discusses the edge-boundary degree of nodes in the reassembling, which is a measure of connectivity and could be relevant to the sub-category of graph theory (cs.GT) that deals with connectivity. Finally, the paper presents an algorithm that runs in linear time, which suggests that the sub-category of algorithms and data structures (cs.SI) may also be relevant.
